{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "15", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "08", "S": "21"}}, "news": [{"title": "Over 15 property owners booked for tenant verification lapses in Samba", "para": "Jammu and Kashmir Police have filed 19 FIRs against property owners in Samba district for failing to provide tenant details. This action stems from a special verification drive aimed at enhancing security and ensuring compliance with mandatory tenant verification norms. The District Magistrate had ordered the police verification of tenants, but owners did not comply, leading to legal action.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/jammu-police-takes-action-against-property-owners-over-tenant-verification-failures/131747877?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-23370/131747877.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "NCZ restoration puts focus on delayed mapping of Aravali, conservation zones", "para": "In April 2022, National Green Tribunal (NGT) had ordered the Board to complete mapping of NCZ. Experts working for protection of Aravali and NCZ in NCR said the Board should expedite the process to comply with the tribunal\u2019s order. While UP and Rajasthan have completed the delineation of NCZ after carrying out the ground truthing exercise, Haryana and Delhi are still in the process of finalising this.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/urgent-mapping-of-aravali-conservation-zones-required-after-ncz-restoration/131748864?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-69118/131748864.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Noida: Residents of Mahagun Moderne oppose common area maintenance fee hike", "para": "Residents of Mahagun Moderne Society protested a hike in maintenance charges. They also raised concerns about blocked fire exits and alleged undemocratic AOA elections. Residents demand accountability and rollback of charges. The AOA president stated the hike complies with government orders and dismissed safety violation claims.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/mahagun-moderne-residents-protest-against-cam-fee-hike-amid-safety-concerns/131748333?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-117512/131748333.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}